But I did go to city hall.

18:35.114 --> 18:36.316
I wanted to speak
to the councilman

18:36.349 --> 18:37.950
about fixing the place up.

18:37.984 --> 18:40.086
Apparently, dude is
getting his hair cut.

18:40.119 --> 18:42.755
-So you are...
-Headed to his barbershop.

18:42.789 --> 18:44.157
My man.

18:44.191 --> 18:45.825
Hey, babe, I got
to finish up here.

18:45.858 --> 18:46.959
I'm buried in work.

18:46.993 --> 18:48.127
All right. I'll see you tonight.

18:56.169 --> 18:58.405
JACK:
You could grow basil for pesto.

19:01.741 --> 19:05.011
When have you ever eaten pesto?

19:12.985 --> 19:15.154
Where are you right now?

19:15.188 --> 19:16.789
What?

19:16.823 --> 19:18.991
Sorry, hon.

19:19.025 --> 19:21.194
I'm right here.

19:23.830 --> 19:25.498
So what do you think
of this place?

19:25.532 --> 19:27.500
Have you noticed Kate's eating?

19:27.534 --> 19:31.704
-Randall...
-You know, and Kevin's
drunk half the time.

19:31.738 --> 19:33.806
But-but you don't seem to care.

19:33.840 --> 19:37.810
I do care.

19:37.844 --> 19:39.712
I'm doing the very best
that I can.

19:39.746 --> 19:41.214
They're both grieving.

19:41.248 --> 19:44.651
-I don't know.

19:44.684 --> 19:47.186
But anything. I mean, you lied.

19:47.220 --> 19:48.988
You said that you'd take care
of everything.

19:49.021 --> 19:50.990
You said we'd be okay,

19:51.023 --> 19:52.191
that you'd step up
and make sure of it,

19:52.225 --> 19:54.160
but you lied.

19:54.193 --> 19:56.563
Mm-hmm.

20:00.199 --> 20:02.168
Yeah.

20:02.201 --> 20:04.203
It's getting late.
I think we need to go.

20:20.387 --> 20:23.189
MIGUEL:
You know, our friend Carol,

20:23.222 --> 20:25.592
she has a daughter
who did the in vitro.

20:25.625 --> 20:26.959
-REBECCA: Mm-hmm. Yeah.

20:26.993 --> 20:30.029
The cute, little twins
with the weird names.

20:30.062 --> 20:32.031
-Eloise and Plaza.

20:32.064 --> 20:33.132
-Yeah.
-REBECCA: Mm-hmm.

20:33.165 --> 20:35.001
Terrible names. Yeah.

20:37.737 --> 20:39.138
-Mom.

20:39.171 --> 20:41.941
Nothing.

20:41.974 --> 20:44.711
Nothing at all, Bug.

20:44.744 --> 20:46.413
This is exactly what
I was trying to avoid.

20:49.015 --> 20:51.418
Just say it.

20:53.986 --> 20:58.825
Kate, have you guys really
considered all of the risks?

20:58.858 --> 21:00.259
Oh, can we not do this?

21:00.293 --> 21:01.961
I'm sure that they've done
the research...

21:01.994 --> 21:04.397
Because I-I did learn a lot
from helping my friend Carol

21:04.431 --> 21:07.434
and I know that
the egg retrieval surgery

21:07.467 --> 21:11.103
is a dangerous procedure
for someone...

21:11.137 --> 21:15.875
someone... your size, Kate.

21:28.154 --> 21:30.156
*

21:31.057 --> 21:34.193
* What did I do wrong?

21:34.226 --> 21:37.196
* Someone tell me...

21:37.229 --> 21:40.199
Excuse me, Councilman Brown,
may I have a word?

21:40.232 --> 21:43.035
A word?

21:43.069 --> 21:45.271
Hell, you can have
a whole paragraph.

21:45.304 --> 21:46.706
My name's Randall Pearson.

21:46.739 --> 21:48.307
I own the property
on Olney and Third.

21:48.341 --> 21:50.209
It's the big one,
right next to the laundromat.

21:50.242 --> 21:52.479
Nice to have a black landlord
in this city.

21:52.512 --> 21:54.381
Not many of those.

21:54.414 --> 21:57.016
Councilman Sol Brown.

21:57.049 --> 21:59.151
-12th District.
-Nice to meet you.

21:59.185 --> 22:00.553
All my pleasure.

22:00.587 --> 22:02.722
My father lived in the building
for several years.

22:02.755 --> 22:05.324
When he passed away,
my wife and I took it as

22:05.358 --> 22:06.859
a personal mission
to turn the place around.

22:06.893 --> 22:09.362
Good for you.
Come on, sit.

22:09.396 --> 22:11.998
-Join us.
-Thank you.

22:12.031 --> 22:15.067
So, what's on your mind,
Mr. Pearson?

22:15.101 --> 22:17.303
I'm actually here about

22:17.336 --> 22:19.539
the rec center on Fifth Street.

22:19.572 --> 22:21.708
The place is falling apart.

22:21.741 --> 22:24.176
I'm talking holes in the wall,
water damage.

22:24.210 --> 22:26.045
The streetlights out front are
either broken or missing.

22:26.078 --> 22:30.316
Yeah, that place isn't
what it was.

22:30.349 --> 22:32.552
Kills me.

22:32.585 --> 22:34.086
What part of town
do you live in?

22:34.120 --> 22:35.922
Oh, I actually live
in New Jersey.

22:35.955 --> 22:38.758
-In the suburbs.
-Oh, good for you.

22:40.460 --> 22:42.995
I grew up in South Philly.

22:43.029 --> 22:45.665
Spent a lot of time at
a rec center myself back then.

22:45.698 --> 22:47.233
Ree's Recreation Center.

22:47.266 --> 22:48.935
-No, I can't say that I have.

22:48.968 --> 22:51.771
My pops owned the grocery store
right across the street from it.

22:51.804 --> 22:54.040
I think I was in high school

22:54.073 --> 22:57.043
when there was a shooting
at Ree's.

22:57.076 --> 22:58.545
The mayor tried
to shut it down,

22:58.578 --> 23:00.246
but my pops wasn't having it.

23:00.279 --> 23:03.450
He always said, "Boy,
ain't nothin' worth having

23:03.483 --> 23:05.618
if you ain't willing
to fight for it."

23:05.652 --> 23:08.187
He got everybody
in the neighborhood

23:08.220 --> 23:10.557
to rally to keep Ree's open.

23:10.590 --> 23:13.593
Your father sounds like
he was the real deal.

23:13.626 --> 23:18.097
He was.
He really was.

23:21.568 --> 23:24.136
Last year, I cast
the deciding vote

23:24.170 --> 23:27.574
to shut Ree's down.

23:27.607 --> 23:32.144
Eh, it wasn't structurally
sound, became dangerous.

23:32.178 --> 23:34.647
In my position, Mr. Pearson,

23:34.681 --> 23:37.049
I have to make decisions
I don't always love.

23:37.083 --> 23:39.051
Ironic, isn't it?

23:39.085 --> 23:41.754
I got into politics
to honor a man

23:41.788 --> 23:44.123
who I'd now be
constantly disappointing.

23:44.156 --> 23:46.425
BROWN:
Hmm.

23:48.427 --> 23:50.062
I'm adopted.

23:50.096 --> 23:54.266
My adoptive father
passed away as well.

23:54.300 --> 23:55.968
So I have two dead fathers

23:56.002 --> 23:58.204
that I'm constantly trying
to make proud.

24:00.206 --> 24:03.142
Tell you what.

24:03.175 --> 24:05.444
I'll have a maintenance crew
come out there today.

24:05.478 --> 24:07.013
I'm gonna be there
to make sure.

24:07.046 --> 24:09.115
Hey, you have my word, brother.

24:09.148 --> 24:10.917
Thank you very much, Councilman.

24:10.950 --> 24:12.151
-My pleasure, son.
-Appreciate it.

24:12.184 --> 24:14.453
Thank you, sir.

24:14.487 --> 24:16.489
*

24:19.125 --> 24:22.529
Hey, all right. Cool.

24:42.515 --> 24:44.517
*

25:12.545 --> 25:14.413
Kevin Pearson, brace yourself.

25:14.446 --> 25:16.148
-Okay, no, here it is.

25:16.182 --> 25:19.552
I found it, so "doctors
will not even perform IVF

25:19.586 --> 25:22.054
on women over a certain weight
in Australia."

25:22.088 --> 25:24.323
-Because it's that dangerous.
-Hi, everyone.

25:24.356 --> 25:26.525
-Oh, hi, sweetheart.

25:26.559 --> 25:27.894
So proud of you.

25:27.927 --> 25:29.528
Really excited for tonight.

25:29.562 --> 25:32.064
Yeah, no, that's-that's obvious.
What's going on here?

25:32.098 --> 25:34.601
Oh, well, uh, Kate and Toby
are getting in vitro,

25:34.634 --> 25:37.336
and your mother knows everything
there is to know about IVF

25:37.369 --> 25:39.038
because of Eloise and Plaza.

25:39.071 --> 25:40.372
The book?

25:40.406 --> 25:41.774
No.

25:41.808 --> 25:43.910
REBECCA:
Kate, I'm just saying,

25:43.943 --> 25:45.177
why would you take that risk
when there are

25:45.211 --> 25:46.545
so many other options
out there?

25:46.579 --> 25:49.015
Because I want to.

25:49.048 --> 25:50.917
'Cause I want to.

25:50.950 --> 25:54.053
Because I want to look
that baby in his face,

25:54.086 --> 25:55.755
and I want to...
I want to see Toby.

25:55.788 --> 25:58.424
I want to see myself.
I want to see--

25:58.457 --> 26:01.093
I want to see Dad.

26:03.229 --> 26:04.697
And I'm the only one
in the family

26:04.731 --> 26:06.633
who's gonna carry on
a piece of Dad.

26:08.000 --> 26:10.970
-Okay, Kev.

26:11.003 --> 26:12.705
"Okay, Kev"? Real--
What's that supposed to mean?

26:12.739 --> 26:15.041
-You're not serious.
-No, no, apparently

26:15.074 --> 26:17.076
I'm not serious ever
about anything.

26:17.109 --> 26:19.045
-This is great...
-Okay, enough, enough, enough.

26:19.078 --> 26:22.114
And, Kate, of course a baby
would be cause for celebration.

26:22.148 --> 26:23.249
But...

26:23.282 --> 26:24.984
-There--

26:25.017 --> 26:26.653
How about stop at "celebration"
and just stop there?

26:26.686 --> 26:28.921
I just think it's irresponsible.

26:28.955 --> 26:30.289
-No.

26:30.322 --> 26:31.924
Yeah, you've already
made that really clear.

26:31.958 --> 26:33.492
No, Kate, now you're
twisting my words.

26:33.525 --> 26:36.095
Okay, well, for the past
20 years,

26:36.128 --> 26:39.799
you have swallowed every single
comment about my weight,

26:39.832 --> 26:41.067
but now, you want to
bring it up now because

26:41.100 --> 26:43.670
-Kate!

26:43.703 --> 26:45.071
Where do I draw the line?

26:45.104 --> 26:47.139
How do I toe the line, Kate,
because--

26:47.173 --> 26:49.942
Shut up!
Everyone just shut up!

26:55.047 --> 26:57.116
This is...
it's not about you, Rebecca.

26:57.149 --> 26:58.084
It's not about any of you.

26:58.117 --> 26:59.886
This is about me and Kate.

27:02.154 --> 27:03.923
All right? We lost a child,

27:03.956 --> 27:05.524
and now we want
to start a family.

27:05.557 --> 27:07.960
And we needed a little help
because we have bad eggs,

27:07.994 --> 27:10.529
and apparently I have
really bad sperm.

27:10.562 --> 27:12.799
So we have every expert in town
telling us

27:12.832 --> 27:14.266
how dangerous this is.

27:14.300 --> 27:17.103
And we know it probably won't
work out for us.

27:17.136 --> 27:18.871
So please, for the love of God,

27:18.905 --> 27:22.074
save the asinine commentary
from the cheap seats.

27:25.644 --> 27:27.313
Toby...

27:27.346 --> 27:29.348
I'm sorry. Look,
I'm gonna, uh...

27:29.381 --> 27:30.717
I'm gonna go clear my head.

27:30.750 --> 27:33.385
I'll see you guys
at the premiere.

27:42.094 --> 27:43.730
That's not how you do it.

27:48.200 --> 27:50.402
Five, six, seven, eight.

27:55.407 --> 27:57.543
WILLIAM: Hi, my name is William,
and I'm an addict.

27:57.576 --> 28:00.412
GROUP:
Hi, William.

28:00.446 --> 28:04.016
I've been clean for five years
and... one minute.

28:06.018 --> 28:08.755
Strange thing to celebrate, huh?

28:08.788 --> 28:11.523
Somehow it feels more special
than my own birthday.

28:11.557 --> 28:16.763
I started using 30 years ago,
when I lost my mother.

28:16.796 --> 28:19.899
The only family
I ever really had.

28:26.038 --> 28:28.941
Then I moved a couple
of blocks away,

28:28.975 --> 28:31.043
and all that changed.

28:31.077 --> 28:34.346
I met Sam,
who drove for Septa

28:34.380 --> 28:36.548
and didn't begrudge me
when I couldn't pay my fare.

28:36.582 --> 28:40.452
And Bernadette, who bested
this old junkie

28:40.486 --> 28:42.054
to a game of chess,
and for her prize

28:42.088 --> 28:44.156
asked that I accompany her
to an NA meeting.

28:46.225 --> 28:47.693
And last night I met

28:47.726 --> 28:50.262
this young Nigerian woman
named ChiChi.

28:53.165 --> 28:56.769
And she let me hold
her beautiful baby.

28:56.803 --> 28:58.905
And she told me
I was a natural.

28:58.938 --> 29:01.607
And it might as well have been
my birthday when she said that.

29:01.640 --> 29:05.011
When she gave me that gift.

29:13.953 --> 29:15.587
WILLIAM:
Community.

29:17.323 --> 29:20.326
That's a strange word
on its own.

29:20.359 --> 29:21.928
The word's not as warm
as "family,"

29:21.961 --> 29:25.097
but some people,
people like myself,

29:25.131 --> 29:27.133
we don't have family.

29:27.166 --> 29:32.504
But that's okay
because we have each other.

29:32.538 --> 29:35.141
We have this place...

29:35.174 --> 29:36.708
and that's not nothin'.

29:39.145 --> 29:41.881
That's not nothin' at all.

29:48.454 --> 29:50.422
I'm going to Ms. Yvette's.

29:50.456 --> 29:51.891
Okay, sweetheart.

29:56.062 --> 29:58.697
Hey, Ma...

29:58.730 --> 30:01.433
I-I'm sorry.

30:01.467 --> 30:03.302
-You know, about before.
-No, no.

30:03.335 --> 30:06.105
No, you don't have to be.
You shouldn't be.

30:06.138 --> 30:08.507
Okay.

30:08.540 --> 30:12.011
Randall...

30:14.746 --> 30:16.015
Randall, it's a struggle for me

30:16.048 --> 30:17.917
to get out of bed
every morning.

30:20.552 --> 30:23.822
It takes every single ounce
of energy that I have,

30:23.856 --> 30:26.158
and then I have nothing left
for the rest of the day.

30:26.192 --> 30:27.994
Nothing.

30:33.933 --> 30:35.968
And I know that isn't fair
to you guys,

30:36.002 --> 30:40.472
but I can't...

30:40.506 --> 30:42.909
seem to stop it.

30:45.544 --> 30:50.482
Huh. Did you know that
your father took me

30:50.516 --> 30:54.553
to look at a new house
a few months before the fire?

30:58.290 --> 31:00.259
Come on, Bec.
What's the harm in looking?

31:00.292 --> 31:02.094
Yeah, I've heard
that one before.

31:04.030 --> 31:07.066
Sometimes I think about where
we would all be right now

31:07.099 --> 31:08.935
if we had bought it.

31:08.968 --> 31:10.736
This house does get
a lot more light

31:10.769 --> 31:12.604
than our place, right?

31:12.638 --> 31:14.373
Yeah, well,
light is overrated.

31:16.608 --> 31:18.177
You could grow
anything you want.

31:18.210 --> 31:22.714
Tomatoes, herbs, maybe some...
maybe some basil for pesto.

31:22.748 --> 31:24.984
Uh, when have you ever
eaten pesto?

31:32.891 --> 31:35.127
Okay, go.

31:35.161 --> 31:38.164
Have fun with your friends...
college boy.

31:39.731 --> 31:41.100
Go.

31:54.013 --> 31:56.815
Okay... we saw it.
Can we go?

31:56.848 --> 31:58.884
-Y-You don't want to see...
-I don't.

31:58.917 --> 32:01.887
I'm sorry, I know
I'm being a bad sport,

32:01.920 --> 32:04.623
but I just--
I love our house, Jack.

32:04.656 --> 32:07.426
Even if it's old
and too small

32:07.459 --> 32:08.894
and doesn't get enough light,

32:08.927 --> 32:10.429
and there isn't any room
to grow basil,

32:10.462 --> 32:14.300
it's... it's our house.

32:14.333 --> 32:17.003
Okay, so we're just gonna
stay there forever?

32:17.036 --> 32:19.405
Sounds pretty good to me.

32:19.438 --> 32:22.941
Me, too. Yeah, I just wanted
to hear you say it.

32:32.384 --> 32:34.353
You sure you don't
want a ride home?

32:34.386 --> 32:37.689
I bought a bus pass. I'm gonna
get my money's worth.

32:37.723 --> 32:40.126
Fixed the light.

32:40.159 --> 32:42.161
I see that.

32:44.196 --> 32:46.465
One down, 8,000 to go.

32:46.498 --> 32:48.000
RANDALL:
I'm gonna stay on him.

32:48.034 --> 32:51.203
We deserve better than this.

32:51.237 --> 32:54.706
I can't figure you out, Randall.

32:54.740 --> 32:56.842
-I loved your father.

32:56.875 --> 33:00.312
He was a good man. We were
his family. He was one of us.

33:00.346 --> 33:05.117
I look at you, Randall,
and oh, my goodness.

33:05.151 --> 33:09.288
I see so much of him in you,
so clearly.

33:09.321 --> 33:13.159
It makes me happy. It gives me
a piece of my friend back.

33:13.192 --> 33:17.163
But we are not a we.

33:17.196 --> 33:19.165
You are not one of us.

33:19.198 --> 33:22.534
You brought your daughter
to come play here,

33:22.568 --> 33:25.337
but instead of sitting
and chatting

33:25.371 --> 33:26.872
and getting to know the place,

33:26.905 --> 33:28.740
you spent the whole day
seeing its problems,

33:28.774 --> 33:30.042
trying to fix them.

33:30.076 --> 33:34.012
I'm not even sure you know why.

33:34.046 --> 33:36.048
We are not our problems.

33:36.082 --> 33:39.085
I know you're not.

33:43.122 --> 33:45.091
I got to get going.

33:45.124 --> 33:47.759
I know you do.

33:54.966 --> 33:57.736
-Oh, wow.
-This is amazing.

33:57.769 --> 34:00.072
-Yeah.
-Toby's not returning my calls

34:00.106 --> 34:02.741
-or answering my texts.
-Ah. No way he misses
a premiere.

34:02.774 --> 34:05.043
He'll be here, trust me.

34:05.077 --> 34:08.380
-Yeah.

34:08.414 --> 34:10.616
I'm really sorry if I hurt
your feelings earlier.

34:10.649 --> 34:13.685
Oh, no, no. Hey, listen,
it's, it's fine.

34:13.719 --> 34:15.254
Okay? I mean, honestly, the idea

34:15.287 --> 34:17.256
of me having kids
makes me physically nauseous.

34:17.289 --> 34:19.458
It wasn't that, it was, um...

34:22.228 --> 34:24.230
He never saw me act.

34:26.565 --> 34:29.034
He was always
the hardest one on me.

34:29.067 --> 34:32.404
And I think it was because he
was the one person in the world

34:32.438 --> 34:34.406
that ever took me seriously.

34:34.440 --> 34:37.143
A-And I always wondered,
you know,

34:37.176 --> 34:39.611
if someone actually gave me
a shot, like, a real shot,

34:39.645 --> 34:41.647
to be the man
that he thought I could be,

34:41.680 --> 34:44.450
if I could actually go there,
if I could actually get there.

34:55.594 --> 34:57.796
And here we are, you know?

34:57.829 --> 35:00.065
In a couple hours,
we'll find out if I deserve

35:00.098 --> 35:03.101
to be taken seriously,
I guess, right?

35:03.135 --> 35:07.105
And now I'm gonna go do
an interview with Mario Lopez.

35:08.540 --> 35:10.742
The world is running
out of water.

35:10.776 --> 35:12.444
It's a major human crisis.

35:12.478 --> 35:14.112
MARIO LOPEZ :
Hey, man, I am hearing nothing

35:14.146 --> 35:16.848
-but positive things, Kevin.
-KEVIN: Good. Good to hear.

35:16.882 --> 35:18.650
-There's a lot
of great buzz right now.
-KEVIN: Thank you.

35:18.684 --> 35:20.819
-You should be excited.
-KEVIN: Thank you. I am excited.

35:20.852 --> 35:22.988
My whole family.

35:23.021 --> 35:24.423
What about a special
lady friend?

35:24.456 --> 35:27.125
-KEVIN: Uh, I just...

35:27.159 --> 35:29.094
-Solo tonight. Just me, just me.
-Okay. All right.

35:29.127 --> 35:30.696
KEVIN:
Uh, I got to ask you a question.

35:30.729 --> 35:32.298
We want to know how you keep
yourself looking so young?

35:32.331 --> 35:34.099
'Cause you look like
you could walk right back

35:34.132 --> 35:35.133
into Saved by the Bell.
I'm not kidding you.

35:37.903 --> 35:40.672
There you are.
Miguel found our seats.

35:40.706 --> 35:42.274
Toby's not here yet.

35:42.308 --> 35:43.775
I don't know
what's going on with him.

35:43.809 --> 35:45.277
I'm sure he'll make it.

35:45.311 --> 35:48.113
No, it's time to take my shot.
And he is supposed

35:48.146 --> 35:50.482
-to give it to me.
-And I'm sure he'll make it.

35:50.516 --> 35:52.318
But it-- if I don't get it
in time, it's gonna throw off

35:52.351 --> 35:54.386
-my whole hormone cycle.
I'm at high risk.
-Okay, Kate, Kate.

35:54.420 --> 35:56.054
One little slip-up
is gonna ruin the whole thing.

35:56.087 --> 35:58.123
Kate.

35:58.156 --> 36:00.192
Do you have it with you?

36:05.096 --> 36:07.966
Just make sure you keep
the site really clean.

36:07.999 --> 36:11.136
I got it. And then
it's just one push, right?

36:11.169 --> 36:12.638
Mm-hmm.

36:17.209 --> 36:21.179
You know, Kate,
after your father passed away,

36:21.213 --> 36:24.015
there was a period of time
where I just didn't...

36:24.049 --> 36:27.085
I didn't know if I was
ever gonna make it back.

36:27.118 --> 36:29.921
You know, if I could make it.

36:29.955 --> 36:31.390
MAN :
Hey, you okay?

36:31.423 --> 36:32.891
WOMAN :
No. Why? Um...

36:32.924 --> 36:34.092
MAN:
You're sure?

36:34.125 --> 36:35.994
It doesn't hurt.

36:36.027 --> 36:39.565
So the thought of anything
ever happening to you,

36:39.598 --> 36:42.167
anything, anything
that could ever put you

36:42.200 --> 36:45.103
in any sort of real harm,

36:45.136 --> 36:48.607
is just paralyzing to me.

36:52.744 --> 36:56.315
You'll see, when you have kids.

36:58.149 --> 36:59.885
WOMAN:
All I can think about was...

36:59.918 --> 37:03.188
I gained 25 pounds.

37:03.221 --> 37:05.023
WOMAN: You know
what it's like when everything

37:05.056 --> 37:07.526
is suddenly different?

37:07.559 --> 37:09.928
And I should have done more

37:09.961 --> 37:12.230
when you really started
gaining the weight.

37:13.999 --> 37:16.268
I was almost 18.

37:17.969 --> 37:23.609
I should have made
better food choices.

37:23.642 --> 37:25.110
WOMAN:
Everything you-you thought...

37:25.143 --> 37:28.447
Well, we've had
a terrible few months.

37:28.480 --> 37:31.717
Don't be so hard on yourself.

37:31.750 --> 37:34.152
WOMAN:
Babbling incoherently

37:34.185 --> 37:37.389
to a strange man.

37:37.423 --> 37:40.459
MAN:
Are you calling me a man?

37:47.633 --> 37:49.635
:
Should we do this? Okay.
-Yeah.

37:52.037 --> 37:54.172
Here we go.

37:56.475 --> 37:59.545
All right.
-KATE: Mm-hmm.

38:00.879 --> 38:04.383
One, two, three.

38:07.819 --> 38:09.355
Okay. Is that okay?

38:09.388 --> 38:12.591
Mm-hmm.

38:12.624 --> 38:15.160
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

38:16.495 --> 38:18.797
Okay.

38:18.830 --> 38:21.700
* Older chests
reveal themselves *

38:21.733 --> 38:23.268
* Like a crack in a wall...

38:23.301 --> 38:25.771
Thank you.

38:25.804 --> 38:27.539
* Starting small

38:30.308 --> 38:32.210
* And grow in time

38:42.354 --> 38:45.323
-Hey.
-* And we always seem

38:45.357 --> 38:47.859
* To need the help

38:47.893 --> 38:49.961
* Of someone else
to mend that shelf... *

38:49.995 --> 38:51.497
-Oh-- ooh!

38:51.530 --> 38:53.865
* Too many books...

38:53.899 --> 38:55.333
Yep.

38:55.367 --> 38:59.037
* Read me
your favorite line... *

39:02.073 --> 39:03.041
* Papa went to other lands...

39:03.074 --> 39:05.877
-Hi. Hi, I'm sorry.
-Babe.

39:05.911 --> 39:09.147
I overreacted, and-and then
I lost track of time.

39:09.180 --> 39:11.049
Do you still need your shot?

39:11.082 --> 39:12.851
My mom did it.

39:12.884 --> 39:14.085
Huh.

39:14.119 --> 39:16.655
-Yeah. Yeah.

39:16.688 --> 39:19.157
I've never seen you
blow up like that. Ever.

39:19.190 --> 39:20.926
What's been going on
with you lately?

39:20.959 --> 39:23.995
Yeah, it's probably
just jet lag.

39:24.029 --> 39:26.031
You know, I'm okay.

39:26.064 --> 39:27.999
All right.
Let's get our seats, yeah?

39:28.033 --> 39:32.203
* Some things,
they stay the same... *

39:33.639 --> 39:35.140
Uh, I'm sorry.

39:38.043 --> 39:40.011
How'd it go at work today?

39:40.045 --> 39:42.247
I kicked that proposal's ass.

39:42.280 --> 39:44.015
That's what's up. Psh...

39:44.049 --> 39:46.051
How'd it go with you?

39:46.084 --> 39:49.354
Uh, it's complicated.

39:49.387 --> 39:51.423
This stuff's always
complicated for me.

39:51.457 --> 39:52.958
What is?

39:52.991 --> 39:55.393
Just where I fit in.

39:55.427 --> 39:57.563
How I come off
to certain people.

39:57.596 --> 40:01.366
It's either I'm trying too hard
or I'm not trying hard enough.

40:01.399 --> 40:04.970
I can never get it right.

40:07.005 --> 40:11.109
* Mama tried to wash
their faces... *

40:11.142 --> 40:13.979
I won't have any fun there.

40:14.012 --> 40:15.581
All right.

40:15.614 --> 40:17.749
* And Daddy lost

40:17.783 --> 40:21.419
* At the races too many times

40:24.456 --> 40:27.425
* She broke down the other day

40:27.459 --> 40:32.430
* Yeah, you know, some things
in life may change *

40:32.464 --> 40:37.769
* But some things,
they stay the same... *

